The Field Technician is a company representative at various Client sites within the Australasia region providing training and technical expertise, maintenance and repairs and support of GroundProbe’s products both locally and globally in surface and underground mining environments.

Responsibilities
1.	Work safely, and with regard to the safety of others, including: 
a.	Compliance with all WHS policies and procedures, and
b.	Actively work to improve safety in the workplace
2.	Install and integrate GroundProbe’s products as required for Customers;
3.	Commission and decommission GroundProbe’s products;
4.	Organise and perform external demonstrations on GroundProbe’s products;
5.	Follow up on demonstrations to ensure successful outcome for Customers and GroundProbe;
6.	Train technical specialist team on deployment, operation and maintenance of GroundProbe’s products;
7.	Manage few customer accounts with technical and operational aspect and build strong relationship with customer
8.	Monitor and present GroundProbe’s products data;
9.	Provide on-site training and technical support to Customers;
10.	Maintain GroundProbe’s products minimising downtime and meeting Customer needs;
11.	Perform technical support work on GroundProbe technologies at remote sites and from GroundProbe’s office;
12.	Assist with marketing and development of a positive image of GroundProbe, its technologies and its employees.

Qualifications
•	Tertiary qualifications or relevant experience in Electrical, Mechanical or Electronic discipline(s);
•	Extensive relevant technical work experience in a customer service based organisation;
•	Experience in electronics, radar, telecommunications or a related field;
•	Experience, proven potential, or a track record of success in a comparable role, doing comparable work.
•	Ability to train individuals and small groups;
•	Mechanical knowledge is desirable.
•	Mining environment/remote location experience is desirable;
•	Computer literacy especially in MS Office;
•	Unencumbered Manual Drivers Licence;
•	Ability to obtain national police clearance certificate for work at mine sites;
•	Ability to pass ongoing Pre-employment medical assessments including drug and alcohol tests for site access.

Salary offer:  The annual salary for this position is $90,000 plus superannuation.

What we offer

As part of a truly global company, you will have the ability to grow and learn in a diverse, collaborative culture. We foster relationships and learning through connected global and local teams, promote flexible and diverse career paths and support the development of your knowledge and skills. 

You will be paid a competitive salary, learn from talented individuals across multiple disciplines and be able to thrive in a safe workplace within a collaborative culture. Ignite your career at a place where your distinct potential can find its home.

Our commitment

GroundProbe promotes and fosters a culture of inclusion and Equal Opportunity Employment everywhere we operate. We treat our people and applicants with fairness, dignity, and respect, getting the best of everyone’s contributions.

All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, religion, sexual orientation, gender perception or identity, nationality, age, military or veteran, marital or disability status.

